<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Doc for Zend_Validate_GreaterThan mention that equal numbers validate with this validator:
{quote}
Basic usage</p>

<p>To validate if a given value is greater than a defined border simply use the following example.</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$valid  = new Zend_Validate_GreaterThan(array('min' =&gt; 10));
$value  = 10;
$return = $valid-&gt;isValid($value);
// returns true
</code></pre>

<p>The above example returns TRUE for all values which are equal to 10 or greater than 10.
{quote}</p>

<p>But both code and tests show that it is not the case.</p>

